From: "Tan, Raymond" <raymond.tan@intel.com>
Date: Mon, 6 Apr 2015 14:08:30 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 29/32] arch: x86: Add new kernel config for X86_INTEL_QUARK

This patch is to add the kernel config CONFIG_ARCH_REQUIRE_GPIOLIB
in the arch kernel config for Intel Quark X1000. This will
enables gpiolib code always get built in.

Signed-off-by: Tan, Raymond <raymond.tan@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Pengyu Ma <pengyu.ma@windriver.com>
---
 arch/x86/Kconfig |    1 +
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/x86/Kconfig b/arch/x86/Kconfig
index c077510..96c2861 100644
--- a/arch/x86/Kconfig
+++ b/arch/x86/Kconfig
@@ -473,6 +473,7 @@ config X86_INTEL_QUARK
 	select IOSF_MBI
 	select INTEL_IMR
 	select COMMON_CLK
+	select ARCH_REQUIRE_GPIOLIB
 	---help---
 	  Select to include support for Quark X1000 SoC.
 	  Say Y here if you have a Quark based system such as the Arduino
